│ ```llvm                                                                                                                      │
│ %call = tail call i32 (ptr, ...) @printf(ptr null, i32 %add1)                                                                │
│ ...                                                                                                                          │
│ %sub3 = add i32 %add2, %call                                                                                                 │
│ %add4 = add i32 %sub3, %0                                                                                                    │
│ store i32 %add4, ptr %k, align 16                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│ This store is part of a sequence of stores that the SLP vectorizer is trying to vectorize.                                   │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The problem is that the SLP vectorizer's scheduler does not correctly handle dependencies on `call` instructions that are    │
│ part of the expression tree being vectorized. Specifically, when a `call` instruction is encountered as an operand, it is    │
│ treated as an external use. The scheduler logic in `BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::schedule` has a special path for external      │
│ uses.                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ When processing an external use, the scheduler calls `decNode()`. This function decrements the `UnscheduledDeps` count for   │
│ the node's dependencies. However, if the external use is a `call` instruction, it has no operands within the vectorization   │
│ tree, so it has no dependencies to decrement. The `decNode()` function is called on a `ScheduleData` object that has already │
│ been fully scheduled (its `UnscheduledDeps` is 0). This leads to `UnscheduledDeps` becoming -1.                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ Later, when the scheduler tries to schedule the node that *uses* the result of the call, it finds that this node has an      │
│ external dependency (the call). It then tries to "unschedule" this dependency by calling `incNode()`, which in turn calls    │
│ `incrementUnscheduledDeps`. At this point, the assertion `UnscheduledDeps >= 0` fails because the dependency's               │
│ `UnscheduledDeps` is -1.                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ **2. Propose a fix**                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The fix is to avoid calling `decNode()` for external uses that are `call` instructions. A `call` instruction, when part of   │
│ the expression tree, acts as a leaf from the scheduler's perspective. It doesn't have operands that are also part of the     │
│ tree, so there are no dependencies within the scheduling graph to account for. Its scheduling is handled by the fact that    │
│ it's an "external use", which prevents reordering past it.                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will modify `BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::schedule` to add a check. Inside the loop that processes external uses, before      │
│ calling `decNode()`, I will check if the external value `E` is a `CallInst`. If it is, I will `continue` to the next         │
│ external use, skipping the `decNode()` call.                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ This change is localized to the scheduling logic and specifically targets the incorrect handling of `call` instructions as   │
│ external dependencies, which directly addresses the cause of the crash.                                                      │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ **3. Implement the fix**                                                                                                     │
